Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Peppermill Resort in Reno, Nevada, thanking mayors for their leadership and discussing the progress made by the Biden administration. She highlighted the importance of local government and the challenges faced by mayors. Harris also talked about the American Rescue Plan and its impact on communities, as well as the efforts to lower the cost of childcare, eldercare, prescription drugs, and gas. She emphasized the need to combat hate and spoke about the rise in hate incidents in recent years. Harris called for unity and common-sense gun safety laws, including renewing the assault weapons ban and expanding background checks. She urged mayors to continue advocating for safer communities and economic opportunities.